edu.nyu.cs.omnidroid.core
Class IntentParser

java.lang.Object
  edu.nyu.cs.omnidroid.core.IntentParser

public class IntentParser
extends java.lang.Object

This class parses the received android.content.Intent's action field to see if it is an OmniDroid supported event. Then it creates an Event object which is able to parse the intent for any associated data attributes.

Method Detail

getEvent

public static Event getEvent(Intent intent)
Given an intent with a supported action type, create and return an Event of the appropriate type. If the action is not supported, null is returned.

Parameters:
intent - an intent received by the system describing the event that took place
Returns:
an OmniDroid Event type that contains the methods to get at the event's data attributes
